   *Loads the "google_site_web" module for domain-to-host reconnaissance.*

5. **Set the module options**:
     ell
   set source example.com
   *Sets the "source" option to "example.com".*

6. **Run the module**:
     ell
   run
   *Executes the loaded module with the set options.*

7. **View the results**:
     ell
    ow hosts
   *Displays the results of the reconnaissance task, such as discovered hosts.*

### Additional Resources

- **Help command**: Use `help` or `help <command>` within the Recon-ng console to get more information about available commands and modules.
- **Documentation**: The official [Recon-ng documentation](https://github.com/lanmaster53/recon-ng) provides comprehensive details on all modules and features.

Feel free to ask if you have any specific questions or need further assistance with Recon-ng!
